T1  - Sexual Harassment as Aggressive Behavior: An Actor-Based Perspective
AU  - O'Leary-Kelly, Anne M.
AU  - Paetzold, Ramona L.
AU  - Griffin, Ricky W.
Y1  - 2000/04/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2000.3312924
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2000.3312924
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 372
EP  - 388
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In research on sexual harassment, authors have given little attention to sexual harassers. The authors of this article present an actor-focused model of sexual harassment interactions. In the model, which is based on interpersonal aggression research, the authors frame sexual harassment as one form of behavior an actor might choose for pursuing valued goals. The model is interactive, in that the authors discuss the effects of sexually harassing actions on the target's perceptions, motives, and behavioral response choice. They also provide propositions to guide future research.
AB  - In research on sexual harassment, authors have given little attention to sexual harassers. The authors of this article present an actor-focused model of sexual harassment interactions. In the model, which is based on interpersonal aggression research, the authors frame sexual harassment as one form of behavior an actor might choose for pursuing valued goals. The model is interactive, in that the authors discuss the effects of sexually harassing actions on the target's perceptions, motives, and behavioral response choice. They also provide propositions to guide future research.
