T1  - Centrifugal and Centripetal Forces in Radical New Product Development Under Time Pressure
AU  - Sheremata, Willow A.
Y1  - 2000/04/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2000.3312925
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2000.3312925
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 389
EP  - 408
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Organizations must be ambidextrous to successfully develop new products?they must act creatively as well as collectively. However, how to do this is not clear. The author analyzes this problem and reviews the literature in terms of two opposing forces: the first increases the quantity and quality of ideas, information, and knowledge available for creative action while the second integrates these things into collective action. The author then models these forces to explain how the coexistence of contradictory structural elements and processes increases the probability of successful development.
