N2  - The emerging information economy is transforming the business landscape. Global information infrastructure, digital technologies, and electronic commerce activities all demand new perspectives regarding business models, strategies, and practices. The book, ?Information Rules: A Strategic Guide to the Network Economy,? by Carl Shapiro and Hal R. Varian is one of a slew of new books attempting to provide those perspectives. The authors have successfully made the book a popular reading for professionals and academics alike by blending in-depth analysis with interesting examples and good managerial insights.
